        },
        "description": "API for accessing CityBikes data including network information, station details, and field filtering. This is a free service providing real-time information about bike sharing networks worldwide.",
        "license": {
          "name": "Terms of Service",
          "url": "https://api.citybik.es/v2/"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "CityBikes API v2",
            "url": "http://api.citybik.es/v2"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "https://api.citybik.es/v2/",
        "title": "CityBikes API",
        "version": "2.0.0",
        "tagline": "Discover bike-sharing networks and real-time station availability for cities worldwide",
        "homepage": "http://api.citybik.es/v2/",
        "docs_url": "http://api.citybik.es/v2/",
        "license_short": "Free to use with required attribution; not strictly open data",
        "license_md": "- Free to access without an API key.\n- Attribution is required: include a noticeable statement on your app or website linking back to the CityBikes project.\n- Projects built on PyBikes should additionally credit that library.\n- The maintainers describe the data as \"not exactly open data\" — attribution is what keeps the service sustainable.",
        "about_md": "[CityBikes](http://api.citybik.es/v2/) is a long-running community project that aggregates real-time data from bike-sharing networks around the world into a single JSON API. The project is powered by the open-source [PyBikes](https://github.com/eskerda/pybikes) scraper library.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- A list of every tracked bike-sharing network with its `id`, `name`, `company`, and location (`latitude`, `longitude`, `city`, `country`).\n- Per-network detail including a `stations` array with each station's coordinates, last-update `timestamp`, and live `free_bikes` / `empty_slots` counts.\n- A `vehicles` array for free-floating systems, with location and a type classifier of `bike`, `ebike`, or `scooter`.\n- Extra metadata where the operator provides it: payment methods, e-bike availability, rental URIs, and online status.\n\nResponses are JSON only. You can trim payloads with the `?fields=id,name,href` query parameter, which selects fields from the top-level document. CORS is enabled, and no authentication is required.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "network": "A bike-sharing system in a given city, exposed at `/v2/networks` (list) and `/v2/networks/{network_id}` (detail with stations and free-floating vehicles)."
        },
